name: Get Windows Information - DEPRECATED
description:
Returns the following information:
    * Windows build name.
    * Date on which Windows has been installed.
    * Display language currently set in Windows.
    * List of the user accounts defined on the local computer.
    * PowerShell, Java, Python and .Net versions.
    * Execution policies for PowerShell.
    * Status of the BitLocker Drive Encryption.
    * Reboot information.

inputs.description: Volume for which the Bitlocker information should be returned (e.g. C)
inputs.name: DiskDrive

outputs.description: Windows build name
outputs.name: WindowsBuild

outputs.description: Date on which Windows has been installed
outputs.name: WindowsInstallDate

outputs.description: Display language currently set in Windows
outputs.name: WindowsDisplayLanguage

outputs.description: List of the user accounts defined on the local computer
outputs.name: WindowsLocalAccounts

outputs.description: PowerShell version (Major.Minor)
outputs.name: PSVersion

outputs.description: Execution policy affecting the remote actions executed by the current Windows PowerShell session. It is set within a PowerShell session via a variable
outputs.name: PSPolicyProcess

outputs.description: Execution policy set through the machine GPO
outputs.name: PSMachinePolicy

outputs.description: Execution policy set through the user GPO
outputs.name: PSUserPolicy

outputs.description: Execution policy affecting only the current user. It is set for the current user on a machine through a registry key
outputs.name: PSPolicyCurrentUser

outputs.description: Execution policy affecting all users of the computer. It is set for the local machine through a registry key
outputs.name: PSPolicyLocalMachine

outputs.description: Indicates whether the volume and its encryption key (if any) are secured
outputs.name: BitLockerProtectionStatus

outputs.description: The status of the encryption or decryption on the volume
outputs.name: BitLockerConversionStatus

outputs.description: The percentage of volume that is currently encrypted
outputs.name: BitLockerPercentageEncrypted

outputs.description: The encryption algorithm and key size used on the volume
outputs.name: BitLockerEncryptionMethod

outputs.description: Lists of protectors used to secure the volume's encryption key
outputs.name: BitLockerKeyProtectors

outputs.description: Date and time of last reboot. It also considers reboots performed while the device was offline (no connection between the Nexthink Collector and the Engine)
outputs.name: LastReboot

outputs.description: Number of days since the last time the machine was rebooted. It also considers reboots performed while the device was offline (no connection between the Nexthink Collector and the Engine)
outputs.name: NumberOfDaysSinceLastReboot

outputs.description: Name of machine startup mode: 'UEFI' or 'BIOS'
outputs.name: StartupMode

outputs.description: Status of Secure Boot feature: 'Yes', 'No', 'Not available'
outputs.name: SecureBootEnabled

outputs.description: Latest version of .Net
outputs.name: DotNetVersion

outputs.description: Default version of Python
outputs.name: PythonVersion

outputs.description: Default version of Java
outputs.name: JavaVersion
